Bug here?
```javascript
function debounce(fn, delay) {
  let timer;
  return function() {
    clearTimeout(timer);
    timer = setTimeout(fn, delay);
  };
}
```

Two issues: `this` context and arguments are lost.

Fix:
```javascript
function debounce(fn, delay) {
  let timer;
  return function(...args) {
    clearTimeout(timer);
    timer = setTimeout(() => fn.apply(this, args), delay);
  };
}
```

Without this, the debounced function ignores any arguments passed and runs with wrong `this` binding.

