Review:
```javascript
function add(a, b) {
  return
    a + b;
}
```

Returns `undefined`. JavaScript's automatic semicolon insertion puts a semicolon after `return`, so `a + b` is dead code.

Fix:
```javascript
function add(a, b) {
  return a + b;
}
```

Never put a line break between `return` and its value.

